Msg 43755 is 08 line(s) on 07/01/90 from WARD CHRISTENSEN
to RICHARD GOZDAL re: R/387 SPEED

 Sure, the '87s are either the same, or the bigger ones are super-sets
of the lower ones. All you have to do is get the right one for your
machine - an 8087 for 8088 or 8086, and 80286 for a 286, and, strangely,
EITHER an 80287 or 80387 for a 386. You said you're running an 80286
and planned an 80387. That won't work, I'm quite sure. The 80387 is
probably a 32 bit bus device.
 What is your application? Do you KNOW that it is HIGHLY dependent
upon floating point ans supports the '87?

